The paper proposes a quantum deep clustering framework based on quantum SVM formulation and deep convolutional neural networks. This work involves quantum computing, machine learning, and data clustering, which are relevant to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with the development of a novel machine learning framework. The second likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a new AI-based approach for clustering. The third likely category is cs.QL (Quantum Physics), as the paper involves quantum computing and quantum SVM formulation. The fourth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed framework. The fifth likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper uses deep convolutional neural networks for feature extraction.
